The inquiry into alleged impropriety at the Public Investment Corporation is set to resume on Monday. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - The inquiry into alleged impropriety at the Public Investment Corporation is set to resume on Monday. The PIC commission is expected to hear more evidence this week. WATCH: PIC inquiry postponed The commission last week heard how three executives, including former CEO Dan Matjila, were reported to the Hawks. Matjila has indicated he wants to respond to allegations against me.